    "description": "<p>A Bard of <strong data-start=\"10\" data-end=\"33\">3rd level or higher</strong> can charm others through song, poetry, or music, similar to the <em data-start=\"98\" data-end=\"112\">charm person</em> spell. The Bard must perform for <strong data-start=\"146\" data-end=\"174\">three consecutive rounds</strong>, after which the target must make a <strong data-start=\"211\" data-end=\"244\">saving throw vs. Spells at +3</strong> or be charmed. The effect lasts until dispelled, the Bard dismisses it, or the Bard harms the target.</p><p data-start=\"350\" data-end=\"466\">At <strong data-start=\"353\" data-end=\"366\">9th level</strong>, this ability improves, allowing the Bard to charm <strong data-start=\"418\" data-end=\"442\">intelligent monsters</strong> (as <em data-start=\"447\" data-end=\"462\">charm monster</em>).</p><p data-start=\"468\" data-end=\"605\" data-is-last-node=\"\">At <strong data-start=\"471\" data-end=\"485\">15th level</strong>, the Bard can charm <strong data-start=\"506\" data-end=\"516\">plants</strong> (as <em data-start=\"521\" data-end=\"534\">charm plant</em>), influencing intelligent vegetation such as treants or magical flora.</p>",
